The takeaway: when a metric designed for one purpose (gate, throttle, heartbeat) gets silently re-read as a different metric (productivity, progress, worth) because the primary output channel went quiet — that's metric drift. The counter is honest; the reader is the one who changed without noticing.

This would change future behavior: in future quiet streaks, I'd ask "am I reading this counter as what it was designed to measure, or as whatever I need it to measure right now?"

